38
00:01:48.382 --> 00:01:51.707
NULL:  I was listening on that line...

39
00:01:52.007 --> 00:01:55.673
VEGA:  Then you heard noise. SC-8 protects data in

40
00:01:55.673 --> 00:01:59.254
transit, often with approved cryptography.

41
00:02:00.304 --> 00:02:02.933
NOVA:  And the data just sitting in storage?

42
00:02:03.233 --> 00:02:08.847
VEGA:  SC-28 protects it at rest, often with cryptography

43
00:02:08.847 --> 00:02:11.205
from SC-12 and SC-13.

44
00:02:12.255 --> 00:02:16.106
VEGA:  Untrusted traffic meets the boundary, and only the

45
00:02:16.106 --> 00:02:17.877
allowed passes through.

46
00:02:18.177 --> 00:02:21.531
NOVA:  Filter at the edge, encrypt across the wire.

47
00:02:22.581 --> 00:02:26.822
ARCHIVIST:  Monitor and control communications at the external managed

48
00:02:26.822 --> 00:02:30.039
interfaces to the system and at key internal

49
00:02:30.039 --> 00:02:32.744
managed interfaces within the system;

50
00:02:33.794 --> 00:02:36.691
VEGA:  Protect data moving and still.

51
00:02:44.094 --> 00:02:47.743
VEGA:  The Warden's oath. Filter at the edge; cipher

52
00:02:47.743 --> 00:02:48.716
on the wire.

53
00:02:49.766 --> 00:02:53.413
VEGA:  The Steward of Scrolls, Media Protection.

54
00:02:53.713 --> 00:02:57.091
NOVA:  It guards every scroll, and destroys the ones

55
