60
00:03:11.039 --> 00:03:17.161
VEGA:  MP-6, media sanitization, ensures deleted really means gone.

61
00:03:17.461 --> 00:03:20.873
NULL:  Your old backup drive would have told me

62
00:03:20.873 --> 00:03:21.811
everything.

63
00:03:22.861 --> 00:03:28.137
VEGA:  And MP-7 controls removable media, the humble USB

64
00:03:28.137 --> 00:03:28.783
stick.

65
00:03:29.833 --> 00:03:33.094
VEGA:  One reading tip before the next gold card.

66
00:03:33.094 --> 00:03:36.355
Notice the brackets in the catalog's text.

67
00:03:36.655 --> 00:03:40.122
NOVA:  So the brackets are blanks the organization fills

68
00:03:40.122 --> 00:03:40.334
in?

69
00:03:40.634 --> 00:03:44.777
VEGA:  Exactly. The requirement is fixed; the value is

70
00:03:44.777 --> 00:03:45.306
yours.

71
00:03:46.356 --> 00:03:51.509
ARCHIVIST:  Sanitize [organization-defined system media] prior to disposal, release

72
00:03:51.509 --> 00:03:55.211
out of organizational control, or release for reuse

73
00:03:55.211 --> 00:04:00.219
using [organization-defined sanitization techniques and procedures] ;

74
00:04:01.269 --> 00:04:04.857
VEGA:  Data outlives the device. Wipe it like you

75
00:04:04.857 --> 00:04:05.541
