83
00:04:35.382 --> 00:04:37.861
NOVA:  What saves us from ransomware?

84
00:04:38.161 --> 00:04:42.118
VEGA:  CP-9, system backup, a clean copy you can

85
00:04:42.118 --> 00:04:43.758
actually restore.

86
00:04:44.058 --> 00:04:46.572
VEGA:  'Clean' is the key word - a backup

87
00:04:46.572 --> 00:04:50.862
kept offline or unchangeable, where ransomware can't reach

88
00:04:50.862 --> 00:04:53.968
it. That's what saved the shipping line we

89
00:04:53.968 --> 00:04:54.855
opened with.

90
00:04:55.905 --> 00:04:59.528
VEGA:  CP-2 is the plan; CP-4 is the drill

91
00:04:59.528 --> 00:05:01.702
that proves it works.

92
00:05:02.752 --> 00:05:07.411
ARCHIVIST:  Conduct backups of user-level information contained in [system

93
00:05:07.411 --> 00:05:09.215
components] [frequency];

94
00:05:10.265 --> 00:05:14.737
VEGA:  Survival is planned in advance, never improvised.

95
00:05:20.565 --> 00:05:23.976
VEGA:  The Keeper's oath. We rehearse the dark, so

96
00:05:23.976 --> 00:05:25.087
